<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. The species described as 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllides longocirrata" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="longocirrata">Syllides longocirrata</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, P." journalOrPublisher="Paul Lechevalier, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Faune de France: Polychetes errantes" year="1923">Fauvel (1923)</bibRefCitation>
actually belongs to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllides fulvus" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fulvus">Syllides fulvus</taxonomicName>
(Marion &amp; Bobretzky, 1875) (
<bibRefCitation author="Parapar, Julio" journalOrPublisher="Nova Acta Cientifica Compostelana (Bioloxia)" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="109 - 123" title="Nuevas aportaciones al conocimiento de los anelidos poliquetos en el litoral gallego (N. O. Peninsula Iberica)" volume="3" year="1992">Parapar et al. 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cinar, Melih Ertan" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="769 - 793" title="Eusyllinae and Syllinae (Annelida: Polychaeta) from northern Cyprus (Eastern Mediterranean Sea) with a checklist of species reported from the Levant Sea" volume="72" year="2003">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Çınar">Cinar</normalizedToken>
and Ergen 2003
</bibRefCitation>
), thus any specimens identified using Fauvel's key probably belong to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllides fulvus" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fulvus">Syllides fulvus</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Campoy, A." journalOrPublisher="Servicio de Publicaciones de la Universidad de Navarra, Pamplona" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Fauna de Espana. Fauna de Anelidos Poliquetos de la Peninsula Iberica" year="1982">Campoy (1982)</bibRefCitation>
considers Mediterranean specimens from soft substrates to belong to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllides fulvus" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fulvus">Syllides fulvus</taxonomicName>
and specimens from hard substrates to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllides edentatus" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="edentatus">Syllides edentatus</taxonomicName>
. Records from Greece are all from soft substrates, thus probably belong to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllides fulvus" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fulvus">Syllides fulvus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
